'''to mouse''' ('''mouses''', '''mousing''', '''moused''')

#{{nautical}} To close the mouth of a [[hook]] by a careful binding of [[marline]] or wire.
#:''Captain Higgins '''moused''' the hook with a bit of [[marline]] to prevent the [[block]] [[becket]]s from falling out under slack.''

===Intransitive verb===
'''to mouse''' ('''mouses''', '''mousing''', '''moused''')

# To move cautiously or furtively, in the manner of a mouse (the rodent); frequently used in the phrasal verb '''to [[mouse around]]'''.
# To hunt or catch mice (the rodents).
